parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause fires, explosions, and loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
Battery failures can cause electrical system malfunctions, fires, and explosions, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
Ignition system failures can cause vehicles to roll or move unexpectedly, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Key can be pulled out of ignition while vehicle is in drive

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: ABS system failures can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the airbag is designed to provide critical protection to the driver and passengers.

despite the severity of the impact.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended deployment of an airbag can cause injuries, distractions, and accidents, especially if it occurs while the vehicle is in motion.
symptoms: often without any apparent reason or crash.

and the seat belt tightens unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The deployment of an airbag with excessive force can cause injuries, especially if it shatters the windshield or causes other damage to the vehicle.
